		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />It's the same 2C02.<br /><br />The only possible variability is the amount of impedance-induced hue rotation, where higher gain (i.e. multiple voltage buffers) might (maybe) reduce the amount of differential phase distortion (i.e. where colors $3x aren't the exact same hue as colors $0x)

		

