	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />You don't <em>need</em> to cut any traces or lift any pins to do that mod. (I didn't.) Everybody seems to report different amounts of jailbars, but I was maybe lucky that they weren't significant for me.<br /><br />The audio signal just comes straight from the audio return pin on the cartridge connector. Only a wire is needed. (I think some people use a small capacitor in line here, though.)<br /><br /><br />As for the jailbars, I wouldn't pay any attention to all the weird suggestions people have for that <em>unless</em> you first do the simple mod and determine that it's a problem for you. A lot of the things people suggest for that seem really complicated (desoldering PPU, etc.) or dubious/superstitious.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


